Tools Used 
Oracle VirtualBox – Virtualization platform used to run both VMs
Windows VM – Used to run Angry IP Scanner and verify IP settings with ipconfig
Kali Linux VM – Used to confirm network configuration with ifconfig
Angry IP Scanner – Tool used to scan the LAN and detect active hosts
Objective
To practice basic network discovery by verifying IP addresses on Windows and Kali, then using Angry IP Scanner to scan the LAN and identify active hosts.  
What I learned
How to verify IP addresses using ipconfig (Windows) and ifconfig (Kali)
How to determine the correct IP range for scanning
How Angry IP Scanner detects active hosts on a LAN
How Windows and Linux machines appear in scan results
How to confirm communication between virtual machines
Fundamentals of network discovery and host enumeration
How virtualization networking works in Oracle VirtualBox
